      • eof

        public boolean eof()

        get whether read reached end of results.

        This method is intended to be used for pagination purposes using range with queries. Every page except the last must return eof = false. This way the client application know when it has reached the last page.
        Returns:
        boolean true if the query returned as many results as present in the database matching the search criteria or false if more results were present but excluded from the results because of explicit limitation of maximum records returned.
